text.section:
Each regular member of a local board shall receive the salary and reimbursement of expenses provided in the county budget, but in no event may the annual compensation be less than the following amounts:
in Allegany County, the amount set by the County Commissioners under Article 24, Title 12, Subtitle 1 of the Code;
in Anne Arundel County, $2,400;
in Baltimore City, $11,000 for the president and $10,000 for other regular members;
in Baltimore County, $4,000 for the president and $3,000 for other regular members;
in Calvert County, $3,000 and reimbursement for expenses in the performance of their duties;
in Caroline County, $3,250 for the president, $3,000 for other regular members, and reimbursement for expenses incurred in the performance of election duties in accordance with the Standard State Travel Regulations;
in Carroll County, $3,000;
in Cecil County, $1,250 for the president, $1,000 for other regular members, and reimbursement for actual expenses incurred in the performance of election activities which occur outside the county;
in Charles County, $800;
in Dorchester County, $3,000 and expenses as authorized by the County Commissioners;
in Frederick County, $5,500 for the president and $5,000 for other regular members;
in Garrett County, the amount set by the County Commissioners under Chapter 91 of the Public Local Laws of Garrett County;
in Harford County, $2,000 for the president and $1,700 for other regular members;
in Howard County, $2,800 for the president and $2,000 for other regular members;
in Kent County, $1,500 for the president and $1,500 for other regular members;
in Montgomery County, $5,000 for the president and $4,500 for other regular members;
in Prince George's County, $5,000 for the president and $4,500 for other regular members;
in Queen Anne's County, $1,500 for the president and $1,200 for other regular members;
in St. Mary's County, $3,000;
in Somerset County, $1,000;
in Talbot County, $600;
in Washington County, the amount set by the County Commissioners;
in Wicomico County, $2,400 for the president and $1,800 for other regular members; and
in Worcester County, $1,500 for the president and $1,200 for other regular members.
